ontrol in a WPF application using version 22.2, you typically need to customize the cell template or apply a style that targets the cell's content. Here's how you can achieve text alignment:

Using Column's CellStyle Property
You can set the CellStyle property of the grid column to align the text to the center. Here's an example:

xml
Copy code
<dxg:GridControl x:Name="grid" AutoGenerateColumns="AddNew">
    <dxg:GridControl.Columns>
        <dxg:GridColumn FieldName="YourFieldName">
            <dxg:GridColumn.CellStyle>
                <Style TargetType="dxg:CellContentPresenter">
                    <Setter Property="HorizontalAlignment" Value="Center"/>
                    <Setter Property="VerticalAlignment" Value="Center"/>
                </Style>
            </dxg:GridColumn.CellStyle>
        </dxg:GridColumn>
    </dxg:GridControl.Columns>
</dxg:GridControl>
Using CellTemplate
If you need more customization, you might consider using the CellTemplate:

xml
Copy code
<dxg:GridColumn FieldName="YourFieldName">
    <dxg:GridColumn.CellTemplate>
        <DataTemplate>
            <TextBlock Text="{Binding YourFieldName}" 
                       HorizontalAlignment="Center" 
                       VerticalAlignment="Center"/>
        </DataTemplate>
    </dxg:GridColumn.CellTemplate>
</dxg:GridColumn>
EditorSettings
For certain column types, you can also use EditorSettings to align text. For example, for a text column:

xml
Copy code
<dxg:GridColumn FieldName="YourFieldName">
    <dxg:GridColumn.EditSettings>
        <dxe:TextEditSettings HorizontalContentAlignment="Center" />
    </dxg:GridColumn.EditSettings>
</dxg:GridColumn>
This approach is useful when you're dealing with editable cells and want the text to be centered both in display and edit modes.

Remember to replace "YourFieldName" with the actual field name you are targeting in your GridControl.

Note
Ensure you have the DevExpress namespace correctly defined in your XAML. For example:
xml
Copy code
xmlns:dxg="http://schemas.devexpress.com/winfx/2008/xaml/grid"
xmlns:dxe="http://schemas.devexpress.com/winfx/2008/xaml/editors"
The exact approach might vary slightly based on the specifics of your grid setup and what you're trying to achieve (e.g., static text alignment vs. alignment in editable cells).
These snippets should help you align text to the center in cells of a DevExpress GridControl in a WPF application. If you run into any issues, refer to the DevExpress documentation for version 22.2 or contact their support for more targeted assistance.



