and i want some columns format to datetime (yyyy-MM-dd HH:Mm:ss)

ChatGPT
To format some columns in a DevExpress GridControl in WPF to display dates in the "yyyy-MM-dd HH:mm:ss" format, you can use the DisplayFormat property of the column. This property allows you to specify how the data should be formatted when displayed in the grid.

Here's an example of how to set this up for a column:

xml
Copy code
<dxg:GridControl x:Name="grid" AutoGenerateColumns="AddNew">
    <dxg:GridControl.Columns>
        <dxg:GridColumn FieldName="YourDateFieldName" Header="Date">
            <dxg:GridColumn.EditSettings>
                <dxe:TextEditSettings DisplayFormat="yyyy-MM-dd HH:mm:ss" />
            </dxg:GridColumn.EditSettings>
        </dxg:GridColumn>
    </dxg:GridControl.Columns>
</dxg:GridControl>
In this example, replace "YourDateFieldName" with the name of the field in your data source that contains the date you want to format. The DisplayFormat attribute in the TextEditSettings tells the grid how to display this field. In this case, it's set to "yyyy-MM-dd HH:mm:ss", which is the format you requested.

Note
This formatting will apply to the display text within the grid cell. If you are using in-place editors or custom templates, you might need to ensure that the editor or template respects this formatting as well.
The EditSettings can be applied to various column types, but the example above uses TextEditSettings for simplicity. Depending on your exact requirements (e.g., if the column is editable and the type of editor you're using), you might choose a different settings class.
Make sure you have the DevExpress namespaces correctly defined in your XAML, similar to the example provided in the previous response.
This approach should help you format date columns in your GridControl as desired. If you encounter any issues, refer to the DevExpress documentation for the specific version you're using, as there might be version-specific features or changes.




